Thought: 1. State Design: Define patterns using an enum for readability. 2. Main Loop: Use a Coroutine with a switch-case block to cycle through patterns and 'yield return' to wait for completion. 3. Implementation: Aimed (vector normalization), Spiral (Trigonometry), Spread (Angle offsets), and Laser (Delayed instantiation of warning/damage objects).

Response:
using System.Collections;
using UnityEngine;

public class BossMonster : MonoBehaviour {
    private enum State { Aimed, Spiral, Spread, Laser }
    private State _state = State.Aimed;
    public GameObject bulletPrefab, L1, L2;
    private Transform player;

    void Start() {
        player = GameObject.FindWithTag("Player").transform;
        StartCoroutine(BossPatternLoop());
    }

    IEnumerator BossPatternLoop() {
        while (true) {
            switch (_state) {
                case State.Aimed: yield return StartCoroutine(PatternAimed()); _state = State.Spiral; break;
                case State.Spiral: yield return StartCoroutine(PatternSpiral()); _state = State.Spread; break;
                case State.Spread: yield return StartCoroutine(PatternSpread()); _state = State.Laser; break;
                case State.Laser: yield return StartCoroutine(PatternLaser()); _state = State.Aimed; break;
            }
            yield return new WaitForSeconds(1.5f);
        }
    }

    IEnumerator PatternAimed() {
        for(int i=0; i<10; i++) {
            Vector2 dir = (player.position - transform.position).normalized;
            Fire(dir); yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.2f);
        }
    }

    void Fire(Vector2 dir) {
        var b = Instantiate(bulletPrefab, transform.position, Quaternion.identity);
        b.GetComponent<Bullet>().SetDirection(dir);
    }
}

Thought: 1. Hard Mode Scaling: Reduce intervals and increase bullet density. 2. New Logic: OverdriveSpiral (dual-direction rotation) and CrossOver (8-way intersecting shots). 3. Optimization: Use TryGetComponent to avoid null reference overhead during high-frequency firing.

Response:
IEnumerator PatternOverdriveSpiral() {
    float angle = 0f;
    for (int i = 0; i < 60; i++) {
        Fire(new Vector2(Mathf.Cos(angle * Mathf.Deg2Rad), Mathf.Sin(angle * Mathf.Deg2Rad)));
        Fire(new Vector2(Mathf.Cos(-angle * Mathf.Deg2Rad), Mathf.Sin(-angle * Mathf.Deg2Rad)));
        angle += 12f;
        yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.03f);
    }
}

void Fire(Vector2 dir) {
    GameObject b = Instantiate(bulletPrefab, transform.position, Quaternion.identity);
    if (b.TryGetComponent<Bullet>(out var script)) script.SetDirection(dir);
}

Thought: 1. Gimmick Design: Boomerang (return logic), Grid (axis-aligned coordinate calculation), Wave (360-degree burst), and Bloom (target-point expansion). 2. Implementation: Utilize nested coroutines and vector math to handle non-linear bullet trajectories.

Response:
IEnumerator BoomerangLogic(GameObject b, Vector2 dir) {
    float t = 0;
    while (t < 1f && b != null) { b.transform.Translate(dir * 5f * Time.deltaTime); t += Time.deltaTime; yield return null; }
    while (t < 2f && b != null) { b.transform.Translate(-dir * 7f * Time.deltaTime); t += Time.deltaTime; yield return null; }
    if (b != null) Destroy(b);
}

IEnumerator PatternWaveRing() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 360; i += 15) {
        float rad = i * Mathf.Deg2Rad;
        Vector2 dir = new Vector2(Mathf.Cos(rad), Mathf.Sin(rad));
        Fire(dir);
    }
    yield return null;
}

Thought: 1. UX Balancing: Increase telegraph (L1) duration and decrease base bullet speed. 2. Safety Zones: Force gaps in circular patterns (e.g., skip shots every 90 degrees) to provide safe spots. 3. Pacing: Set post-pattern delay to 2.5s or more.

